.tactic = arch:directional-deps

.what
enforce top-down dependency flow; lower layers must not import from higher ones

.scope
applies to src/ folders and modules; required for contract/, access/, domain.objects/, domain.operations/; governs imports and references

.why
upholds separation of concerns and clean architecture; prevents circular dependencies; eases tests and isolation; aligns with arch:bounded-contexts for orchestration

.structure
```
src/
  contract/          // public interfaces
    api/             // public endpoints
    cmd/             // internal entrypoints
    sdk/             // public exports
    cli/             // public cli contracts

  access/            // infrastructure layer
    daos/            // persistence logic
    sdks/            // third party contracts
    svcs/            // first party contracts

  domain.objects/    // domain declarations
  domain.operations/ // domain behavior

  infra/             // adapters
```

.how
each layer depends only on layers below; contract/ on domain.objects/ and domain.operations/; access/ on domain.objects/ and domain.operations/; domain.operations/ on domain.objects/ or infra/; domain.objects/ and infra/ self-contained; stitched flows in domain.operations/ or contract/cmd/; no upward imports; shared types follow rules

.enforcement
upward imports = blocker; circular dependencies = blocker; domain.objects/ isolated; domain.operations/ uses only infra/ adapters; access/ free of business rules; infra/ free of domain knowledge

.examples

